c-summary"></div><div class=3D"sc-eeDRCY sc-eBMEME gvJSKt cCHnVo" data-role=
=3D"redoc-description"><p>Welcome to the <strong>WeezPay API Documentation<=
/strong>.  </p>
<p>The main goal of this API is to allow external parties to talk with the =
WeezPay server for various kind of actions.
The API provides the way to set up some configurations, to create or retrie=
ve wallets and their information,
to create and record transactions, make sales...</p>
</div></div></div></div><div id=3D"section/Information" data-section-id=3D"=
section/Information" class=3D"sc-dcJsrY hYxaue"><div class=3D"sc-kAyceB XMn=
SL"><div class=3D"sc-fqkvVR ecXCOZ"><h2 class=3D"sc-jXbUNg iOsDVn"><a class=
=3D"sc-jlZhew jrsfjb" href=3D"https://docapi.weezevent.com/openapi.html?wee=
zpay#section/Information" aria-label=3D"section/Information"></a>Informatio=
n</h2></div></div></div><div id=3D"section/Information/Version-philosophy" =
data-section-id=3D"section/Information/Version-philosophy" class=3D"sc-dcJs=
rY hYxaue"><div class=3D"sc-kAyceB XMnSL"><div class=3D"sc-fqkvVR ecXCOZ"><=
h2 class=3D"sc-dhKdcB iYyRkp"><a class=3D"sc-jlZhew jrsfjb" href=3D"https:/=
/docapi.weezevent.com/openapi.html?weezpay#section/Information/Version-phil=
osophy" aria-label=3D"section/Information/Version-philosophy"></a>Version p=
hilosophy</h2></div></div><div class=3D"sc-fqkvVR cDVEeq"><div class=3D"sc-=
eeDRCY sc-eBMEME gvJSKt cCHnVo redoc-markdown "><p>In order to limit the ve=
rsions of the API, we decided to keep the same version as long as possible =
without breaking change.
So, for the same version, we could add new optional fields or new endpoints=
 but we should not make any breaking change.
You are advised to check this documentation time to time to get the last up=
dates.  </p>
<p>Note a big change about how to pass the version to our API:</p>
<ul>
<li>Previously:  <ul>
<li>The version was passed in <code>Nemopay-Version</code> header, that's n=
ow deprecated, but still maintained for a while.</li>
<li>The format of the version was a string date.</li>
<li>If you omit to pass the version, you got an error.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>From now on:<ul>
<li>The version is passed in the url after <code>/pay</code>.</li>
<li>The format swtiched to <code>v1</code>, <code>v2</code>, <code>v3</code=
>... <code>v1</code> is the current stable version (previously called <code=
>2020-12-01</code>),
<code>v2</code> is still in progress and a few endpoints are now stable and=
 recommended to be used.</li>
<li>if you omit to pass the version (keeping the url without the version af=
ter <code>/pay</code>),
then by default the API uses the stable version, that is to say, <code>v1</=
code> for now.
However it's recommended to stuck the version on the url to prevent any bre=
ak when the <code>v2</code> will become the stable one (in some monthes).</=
li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</div></div></div><div id=3D"section/Information/Authentication-and-authori=
zation-(permissions)" data-section-id=3D"section/Information/Authentication=
-and-authorization-(permissions)" class=3D"sc-dcJsrY hYxaue"><div class=3D"=
sc-kAyceB XMnSL"><div class=3D"sc-fqkvVR ecXCOZ"><h2 class=3D"sc-dhKdcB iYy=
Rkp"><a class=3D"sc-jlZhew jrsfjb" href=3D"https://docapi.weezevent.com/ope=
napi.html?weezpay#section/Information/Authentication-and-authorization-(per=
missions)" aria-label=3D"section/Information/Authentication-and-authorizati=
on-(permissions)"></a>Authentication and authorization (permissions)</h2></=
div></div><div class=3D"sc-fqkvVR cDVEeq"><div class=3D"sc-eeDRCY sc-eBMEME=
 gvJSKt cCHnVo redoc-markdown "><p>Authentication and authorization documen=
tation is provided in the 'Authorizations' section for every single endpoin=
t.  </p>
<h3 id=3D"authentication">Authentication</h3>
<p>For WeezPay API server, the client that request resources can be authent=
icated as:</p>
<ul>
<li>an <strong>application</strong> with no user, basically for 'server to =
server' exchanges.</li>
<li>an <strong>user</strong> through an <strong>application</strong>.</li>
<li>an <strong>user</strong> under no application.</li>
</ul>
<p>Whatever the type of client that request the WeezPay API server,
we have multiple types of <strong>authentication</strong> possible, well do=
cumented for every endpoints:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>OAuth2</strong> authentication (client credentials flow): you g=
et an access token from a dedicated trusted authentication server
as for example the Weezevent Accounts authentication server <a href=3D"http=
s://docapi.weezevent.com/openapi.html?weezpay#tag/OAuth-2.0-Weezevent-Accou=
nts">(see section below)</a>.
Once got, you provide the access token thanks to the Bearer token authentic=
ation.</li>
<li><strong>Bearer token</strong> authentication (also used as the final pa=
rt of the OAuth2 authentication):
you provide the authentication token prefixed by <code>Bearer &lt;your-toke=
n&gt;</code> in the HTTP header <code>Authorization</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Session ID</strong>: you provide the session ID (which is a kin=
d of token generated directly by the WeezPay server for the user session)
prefixed by <code>Session &lt;your-session-id&gt;</code> in the HTTP header=
 <code>Authorization</code>.
To get a session Id, a basic authentication (email address / password) is r=
equired formerly.</li>
<li>Cookie <strong>(deprecated)</strong>: you provide the session ID (which=
 is a kind of token generated directly by the WeezPay server for the user s=
ession).
in a cookie named <code>sessionid</code>. This method is deprecated. You mu=
st not use it.
To get a session Id, a basic authentication (email address / password) is r=
equired formerly.</li>
<li><strong>None</strong>: Some endpoints do not require any authentication=
. Sometime we call that the 'anonymous' authentication.
If so, the authentication section (called 'Authorizations') in the endpoint=
 documentation won't be provided.</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p>If you request an endpoint that requires an authentication and you are n=
ot,
the server will respond with the HTTP code 401 (unauthorized).</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id=3D"authorization-permissions-and-rights">Authorization (permissions =
and rights)</h3>
<p>As regards <strong>authorization (permissions and rights)</strong>, thos=
e are set by the administrator
at the application and/or user level directly in the WeezPay API server.
Consequently, you don't need to take care about that during authentication,
the token or the session ID you will get is valid and usable for all types =
of action / resources you are allowed for.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>If you are authenticated and you request an endpoint that requires a per=
mission / right you don't have,
the server will respond with the HTTP code 403 (forbidden).</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The permissions required are describes as <code>required scopes</code> i=
n the authentication section of the endpoint documentation.
When multiple, the client must be granted at least for one permission, not =
all are required.<br>Here is the list of the permissions the client (applic=
ation and/or user) can be granted:</p>
<ul>
<li>None: The user / application must be authenticated but does not require=
 any specific permission,
it will get the resources filtered according to it.</li>
