<div class=3D"sc-fqkvVR cDVEeq"><div class=3D"sc-eeDRCY sc-eBMEME gvJSKt cC=
HnVo redoc-markdown "><p>In WeezPay, the money, the amounts that are exchan=
ged in the system is related to a currency as it is in the 'real' world.
The concept of currency is actually defined by two models: the <strong>curr=
ency group</strong> and the <strong>currency</strong>.  </p>
<ul>
<li>A <strong>currency group</strong> is acutally what we understand as a c=
urrency in the 'real' world.
The properties of a currency group are basically a name, a symbol and a num=
ber of decimals (decimal places).  </li>
<li>A <strong>currency</strong> can be actually understood more or less as =
a sub-currency.
It holds the same properties as the groups it belongs to, but it can also d=
efine specific properties or usage restrictions.
Conceptually, every single currency managed in cashless transactions should=
 be understood as a 'token' currency.</li>
</ul>
<p>Note that the currency with the ID 1 that belongs to the currency group =
with the ID 1 is defined as the 'main' or 'default' currency in the system.=
<br>This is the only 'token' currency that is directly related to the 'real=
' currency (the one used in the 'real world as EUR, GBP...),
used for payments, top-ups or refunds. Optionally, an exchange rate can be =
defined between the 'token' currency and the 'real' currency.</p>
</div></div></div><div id=3D"tag/Currencies-and-currency-groups/operation/g=
