Please take care to append <code>v2</code> in the url instead of <code>v1</=
code>.
Any new feature or new endpoint is now implemented in v2.
Anyway, we want to provide these new features to third parties, that's why =
we added it in this documentation (v1)
with this note, waiting for the public release of v2.
There are different available action types:</p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li><code>CANCEL_TRANSACTION</code>: to cancel a transaction totally.<ul>
<li>permissions:<code>GESSALES</code>,<code>TRESO</code>,</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><code>CANCEL_TRANSACTION_PARTIALLY</code>: to cancel only specific rows=
 (totally or partially) of a transaction.<ul>
<li>permissions:<code>GESSALES</code>,<code>TRESO</code>,</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><code>CANCEL_TRANSACTION_PARTIALLY_REFUNDABLES</code>: to cancel only r=
efundable rows (totally or partially) of a transaction.<ul>
<li>permissions:<code>GESCANCELREFUNDABLES</code>,<code>GESSALES</code>,<co=
de>TRESO</code>,</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><code>CREATE_TRANSACTION</code>: to create and register a transaction t=
hat has already been paid (not cashless).<ul>
<li>permissions:<code>GESSALES</code>,<code>TRESO</code>,</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><code>CREATE_TRANSACTION_AND_PAY_CASHLESS</code>: to create and registe=
r a transaction byprocessing the payment (in cashless) for the given wallet=
.<ul>
<li>permissions:<code>GESSALES</code>,<code>TRESO</code>,</li>
</ul>
</li>
