VR cDVEeq"><div class=3D"sc-eeDRCY sc-eBMEME gvJSKt cCHnVo redoc-markdown "=
><p>A <strong>wallet</strong> is the core of the cashless concept. We can s=
ay it represents a specific attendee or person that uses the cashless syste=
m.
Indeed a wallet has one or multiple balances (one per currency), it is link=
ed to one specific chip (tag),
it can link zero, one or multiple ticket barcodes... also it is holds some =
access rights, some rules, some restrictions...<br>In order to manage the s=
ame rights, restrictions or rules for multiple wallets, we can put them to =
what we call a <strong>wallet group</strong>.  </p>
<p>It should not be mixed-up with an user. An user can hold zero, one or se=
veral wallets
