 class=3D"sc-eeDRCY sc-eBMEME gvJSKt cCHnVo redoc-markdown "><p>WeezPay pro=
vided some webhooks in order to notify the clients they want to be,
depending on the type of action that has been done in its cashless system.<=
br>The type of action we manage are:  </p>
<ul>
<li>top-up  </li>
<li>transaction (sale)  </li>
<li>transfer (between two wallet balances)  </li>
<li>wallet update</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"configuration">Configuration</h3>
<p><em>Currently the webhooks need to be configured by your contact at Weez=
event,
but they will be soon configurable through API and an admin panel in Weezev=
ent ecosystem.</em>  </p>
<p>In order to configure the webhooks, we need from you an https endpoint w=
here we will <code>POST</code> the given body.
You can optionally provide a secret that we will use to add a signature hea=
der on this <code>POST</code>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"errors-and-retrials">Errors and retrials</h3>
<p>Currently in case of error (your endpoint not giving a 200), there is no=
 retry system in place.
But we store the error in our side.
In case of special request from you, we are able to reprocess the failed me=
ssage to send it you again.
It's plan in future to add some auto-retry rules.</p>
<h3 id=3D"body-and-fields">Body and fields</h3>
<p>The documentation gives the description of the default content message p=
osted and related to WeezPay.  </p>
<p>The body content is customizable in our system through customized format=
ter,
so for special need, it's possible to rename or get rid of some fields.
Just let us know.  </p>
<p>=E2=9A=A0 Webhooks are new, documentation may need to be stabilized.
Some fields may not be documented or slightly different.
We will do our best to never remove/rename existing field, and only adding =
new fields when needed.</p>
